def ricker(data):
    """Multiply freq-result with Ricker wavelet.
    
    For the time-domain result, this is done in empymod.model.gpr.
    """
    cf = 250e6
    cfc = -(np.r_[0, f[:-1]]/cf)**2
    fwave = cfc*np.exp(cfc)
    return data*fwave[:, None]

Parameters as in Hunziker et al., 2015

In [4]:
f = np.linspace(0.5, 850, 300)*1e6
finp = {'src': [0, 0, 0.0000001],
        'rec': [[0.2, 2.0, 3.0], [0, 0, 0], 0.5],
        'depth': [0, 1],
        'res': [2e14, 200, 20],
        'ab': 11,
        'epermH': [1, 9, 15],
        'epermV': [1, 9, 15],
        'loop': 'off', 'verb': 2, 'freqtime': f, 'opt': 'spline'}
In [5]:
try:
    fgprDLF = np.load('data/GPR-DLF-Frequency.npy')
except:
    fgprDLF = epm.dipole(ht='fht', htarg=epm.fdesign.load_filter('wer2001'), **finp)
    fgprDLF = ricker(fgprDLF)
    np.save('data/GPR-DLF-Frequency', fgprDLF)
try:
    fgprQUA = np.load('data/GPR-QUA-Frequency.npy') 
except:
    fgprQUA = epm.dipole(ht='quad', htarg=['', '', 51, '', 160, 500], **finp)
    fgprQUA = ricker(fgprQUA)
    np.save('data/GPR-QUA-Frequency', fgprQUA)

# Load data

Plot¶

In [7]:
plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
xlim = [1, 850]

# f-domain

# 1: x = 0.2 m ; Response
plt.subplot(231)
plt.title('(a) Hor. offset = 0.2 m')
plt.ylabel('Real part')
plt.plot(f/1e6, fgprQUA[:, 0].real, '.7', lw=2, label='QUAD')
plt.plot(f/1e6, fgprDLF[:, 0].real, 'k:', lw=1, label='Re(DLF)')
plt.plot(f/1e6, fgprQUA[:, 0].imag, '.7', lw=2)
plt.plot(f/1e6, fgprDLF[:, 0].imag, 'k--', lw=1, label='Im(DLF)')
plt.xlim(xlim)
plt.xlabel('Frequency (MHz)')

# 2: x = 2 m ; Response
plt.subplot(232)
plt.title('(b) Hor. offset = 2 m')
plt.plot(f/1e6, fgprQUA[:, 1].real, '.7', lw=2, label='QUAD')
plt.plot(f/1e6, fgprDLF[:, 1].real, 'k:', lw=1, label='Re(DLF)')
plt.plot(f/1e6, fgprQUA[:, 1].imag, '.7', lw=2)
plt.plot(f/1e6, fgprDLF[:, 1].imag, 'k--', lw=1, label='Im(DLF)')
l = plt.legend(loc=8, bbox_to_anchor=(-0.1, -.05))
l.get_frame().set_alpha(1)
plt.xlim(xlim)
plt.xlabel('Frequency (MHz)')

# 3: x = 3 m ; Response
plt.subplot(233)
plt.title('(c) Hor. offset = 3 m')
plt.plot(f/1e6, fgprQUA[:, 2].real, '.7', lw=2, label='QUAD')
plt.plot(f/1e6, fgprDLF[:, 2].real, 'k:', lw=1, label='Re(DLF)')
plt.plot(f/1e6, fgprQUA[:, 2].imag, '.7', lw=2)
plt.plot(f/1e6, fgprDLF[:, 2].imag, 'k--', lw=1, label='Im(DLF)')
plt.xlim(xlim)
plt.xlabel('Frequency (MHz)')


# t-domain
xlim = [1, 80]

# 1: x = 0.2 m ; Response
plt.subplot(234)
plt.title('(d) Hor. off. = 0.2 m')
plt.ylabel('Amplitude')
plt.plot(t*1e9, gprQUA[:, 10], '.7', lw=2, label='QUAD')
plt.plot(t*1e9, gprDLF[:, 10], 'k:', lw=1, label='DLF')
plt.xlabel('Time (ns)')
plt.xlim(xlim)

# 2: x = 2 m ; Response
plt.subplot(235)
plt.title('(e) Hor. off. = 2 m')
plt.plot(t*1e9, gprQUA[:, 100], '.7', lw=2, label='QUAD')
plt.plot(t*1e9, gprDLF[:, 100], 'k:', lw=1, label='DLF')
plt.xlabel('Time (ns)')
plt.legend()
plt.xlim(xlim)

# 3: x = 3 m ; Response
plt.subplot(236)
plt.title(r'(f) Hor. off. = 3 m')
plt.plot(t*1e9, gprQUA[:, 150], '.7', lw=2, label='QUAD')
plt.plot(t*1e9, gprDLF[:, 150], 'k:', lw=1, label='DLF')
plt.xlabel('Time (ns)')
plt.xlim(xlim)

plt.tight_layout(h_pad=2, w_pad=-2)

# Save figure and show it
plt.savefig('../figures/ftGPR.pdf', bbox_inches='tight')
plt.show()

# Multiply with ricker wavelet
cf = 250e6
cfc = -(np.r_[0, f[:-1]]/cf)**2
fwave = cfc*np.exp(cfc)
fgprDLF2 *= fwave[:, None]
fgprQUA2 *= fwave[:, None]
